theorem isOpen_of_isClosed_of_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed A → Topology.P3 A → IsOpen A := by
  intro hClosed hP3
  -- From `P3` and the closedness of `A`, we have the inclusion `A ⊆ interior A`.
  have h1 : A ⊆ interior A := by
    simpa [hClosed.closure_eq] using
      (hP3 : A ⊆ interior (closure A))
  -- The interior is always contained in the set itself.
  have h2 : interior A ⊆ A := interior_subset
  -- Hence `interior A = A`.
  have h_eq : interior A = A := subset_antisymm h2 h1
  -- Since `interior A` is open, `A` is open as well.
  simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior

theorem P2_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P2 (interior (closure A)) := by
  have hOpen : IsOpen (interior (closure A)) := isOpen_interior
  exact Topology.isOpen_P2 (A := interior (closure A)) hOpen
